11
[p 
	"Arumana no Kiseki is an FDS only platformer with an interesting grappling hook mechanic. Perhaps not surprisingly for a rather complicated mechanic like this one, it is abused heavily to clip through walls and most of several levels.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"This run is an update of mmbossman's original, with improved boss fights, implementing the improvement missed in the original submission, and better control over scrolling in level 3.     
	$LF
]p
[pre 
	$LF
]pre
[h3 
	" Game objectives
	$LF
]h3
[ul 
	[li 
		" Emulator used: FCEUX 2.2.2
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Beats the game as fast as possible
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[p 
	"Temp Encode:
	$LF
	(youtube|v=9BxtZHHlLv0)
	$LF
]p
[h3 
	" Improvements
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	[b 
		"Stage 1:
	]b
	" mmbossman had missed an animation cancel in the original run, so this is the first thing I improved.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"Stage 2:
	]b
	" I saved a few frames on the boss.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"Stage 3:
	]b
	" I saved quite a few frames optimizing the climb, keeping the screen scrolling as much as possible.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"Stage 4:
	]b
	" nothing new, but re-syncing the boss fight was pretty tough
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"Stage 5:
	]b
	" I made the boss spawn sooner, which saved about 10 frames.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"Stage 6:
	]b
	" nothing new
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"Total improvement:
	]b
	" 102 frames
	$LF
]p
[h3 
	" Other comments
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"I stumbled upon this run while browsing through 
	[a href=/Movies-NES-FDS-Stars-Moons 
		"this list.
	]a
	$LF
	"I noticed that this run had no youtube encode (despite it being the very first run.)
	$LF
	"Looking at the submission thread, I noticed the improvement right at stage one. Since I don't like seeing known improvements just sitting un-implemented, I decided to pick it up and ended up saving a bit more time as well. I guess you could say I like spring cleaning.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Re-syncing the spider boss was the hardest part, luckily brute force saved me, although it took many thousands of re-records to do so.
	$LF
